# Local-only material. These exist on the team's machines but are deliberately
# not published: the repository carries the application, the acceptance checks and
# the report, and nothing else.
#   deploy/       the proxy + tunnel scripts that put the local model behind a
#                 public hostname. Local operations, not part of the deployed app.
#   DEPLOY.md     the runbook for the above.
#   PRESENTATION.md  speaker notes.
#   docs/         working notes.
#   .devcontainer/ Codespaces boilerplate. It also pinned Python 3.11, which the
#                 pins in requirements.txt do not work on.
#   report/REPORT.md  the prose draft REPORT.tex was typeset from. Two copies of
#                 one document drift - that is how a figure caption came to
#                 describe a chart the report did not contain - so the .tex is
#                 the single source and the draft stays local.
deploy/
DEPLOY.md
PRESENTATION.md
docs/
.devcontainer/
report/REPORT.md

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Environment: .env holds the LM Studio URL, which differs per machine.
# .env.example is committed; .env is not.
.env

# Streamlit secrets carry the real proxy token. Only the example is committed.
.streamlit/secrets.toml

# Generated artefacts. All of these are rebuilt by:
#   python -m scripts.check_task_c
#   python -m scripts.export_report_assets
exports/

# LaTeX build intermediates. REPORT.tex and the built REPORT.pdf ARE committed -
# the PDF is the submitted deliverable (M5) and a marker should not need a TeX
# installation to read it. Everything latexmk regenerates is not.
*.aux
*.fdb_latexmk
*.fls
*.log
*.out
*.synctex.gz
*.toc

# The dataset (2.2 MB, public sample data) IS committed. A deployed instance has
# no local filesystem to fetch it into, so the app cannot start without it.
# Any other CSV dropped into data/ stays local.
data/*.csv
!data/superstore.csv

# Benchmark output is regenerated by scripts/check_task_b.py, but the historical
# runs ARE committed on purpose - the 5/10 -> 9/10 -> 10/10 progression is
# evidence for the report and must not be lost.
!benchmarks/results_run*.csv

# Editors / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
deploy/.run/
